[[Category:Heian Period events]] [[Category:Kyoto in the Heian period]] [[Category:Lightning strike incidents]] [[Category:Emperor Daigo]] [[Category:Sugawara no Michizane]] [[Category:Japan in 930]] [[Category:10th-century disasters]] [[Category:completion tier 1]] [[Category:Https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/]][[zh:%E6%B8%85%E6%B6%BC%E6%AE%BF%E8%90%BD%E9%9B%B7%E4%BA%8B%E4%BB%B6]] [[ja:清涼殿落雷事件]]

{{Infobox event | title = <!-- Display title (if different from the article title) --> | image = [[file:Kitano Tenjin Engi Emaki - Jokyo - Thunder God.jpg|400px|center]][[file:Kitano Tenjin Engi Emaki - Jokyo - Thunder God2.jpg|400px|center]] | caption = Depicted in the “Kitano Tenjin Engi Emaki”, the Seiryōden Lightning Strike Incident | date = {{ill|Enchō (era)|ja|延長 (元号)|lt=Enchō|lt_ja=延長}}8年 {{ill|June 26 (lunar calendar)|ja|6月26日 (旧暦)|lt=June 26|lt_ja=6月26日}} ({{ill|930 AD|ja|930年}} {{ill|July 24|ja|7月24日}}) | time = 16:00 - 16:30 | location = {{ill|Heian-kyō|ja|平安京}} {{ill|Imperial Palace|ja|内裏}} {{ill|Seiryōden|ja|清涼殿}} | reported deaths = 3–5 persons ({{ill|Fujiwara Kiyokan|ja|藤原清貫}}, {{ill|Taira Kiyose|ja|平希世}}, Minu Tadakazusa (美努忠包), {{ill|Imperial Guard Office|ja|近衛府|lt=Guard|lt_ja=近衛}} 2 persons?) | reported injuries = 2–4 persons (Kikinren, Azumi Sōjin, 2 persons of Konoe?) | reported property damage = South eave of Seiryōden burned }}
'''Seiryōden Lightning Strike Incident''' (清涼殿落雷事件) is a lightning strike disaster that occurred during the {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代}}, in the 8th year of {{ill|Enchō (era)|ja|延長 (元号)|lt=Enchō|lt_ja=延長}} on {{ill|June 26 (lunar calendar)|ja|6月26日 (旧暦)|lt=June 26|lt_ja=6月26日}} ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} {{ill|930 AD|ja|930年}} {{ill|July 24|ja|7月24日}}) at {{ill|Heian-kyō|ja|平安京}} – {{ill|Imperial Palace|ja|内裏}} – at {{ill|Seiryōden|ja|清涼殿}}, where a lightning strike occurred.
== Overview == That year, the area around {{ill|Heian-kyō|ja|平安京}} was afflicted by a {{ill|drought|ja|旱魃|lt=Drought damage|lt_ja=干害}}, and on June 26 a meeting of the {{ill|Great Council of State|ja|太政官}} was held at Seiryōden, where {{ill|Emperor Daigo|ja|醍醐天皇}} was present, to discuss whether to perform a {{ill|rainmaking ritual|ja|雨乞い}}.<ref>『日本紀略』延長8年5月15日、6月</ref> However, shortly after noon, dark {{ill|cumulonimbus|ja|積乱雲|lt=black clouds|lt_ja=黒雲}} suddenly gathered above {{ill|Mount Atago (Kyoto)|ja|愛宕山 (京都市)|lt=Atago}}, covering Heian-kyō and unleashing a violent {{ill|thunderstorm|ja|夕立|lt=Thunderstorm|lt_ja=雷雨}}.<ref name="kiryaku">『日本紀略』延長8年6月26日</ref> Shortly after 16:00, lightning directly struck the first pillar on the southwest side of Seiryōden.<ref name="fusob">『扶桑略記』裏書 延長8年6月26日</ref><ref name="kiryaku" />
At that time, courtiers ({{ill|kuge|ja|公卿}}) and officials ({{ill|kanjin|ja|官人}}) present were caught up in the incident. Among the courtiers, {{ill|Dainagon|ja|大納言}} and {{ill|Minister of Popular Affairs|ja|民部省（律令制）|lt=Minbu-kyo|lt_ja=民部卿}} {{ill|Fujiwara Kiyokan|ja|藤原清貫}} had his garments set on fire and his chest torn open, dying instantly, while {{ill|Right Middle-Border|ja|右中弁}} and {{ill|Internal Storage Head|ja|内蔵頭}} {{ill|Taira Kiyose|ja|平希世}} suffered facial burns and was left in critical condition. Shortly after 16:30, as the rain ceased, Kiyokan was secretly transported by carriage from {{ill|Yōmyōmon|ja|陽明門}}, and Kiyose from {{ill|Shūmyōmon|ja|修明門}}; however, Kiyose soon died.
The lightning also struck the adjacent {{ill|Shishinden|ja|紫宸殿}}, and {{ill|Uhyōesa|ja|右兵衛佐}} Minu Tadakazusa (in the {{ill|Fusō Ryakki|ja|扶桑略記}}, identified as {{ill|Ukonoe Tadakane|ja|右近衛忠兼}} in that account) had his hair burned and died. Kikinren suffered burns to his abdomen and writhed in agony, and Azumi Sōjin had his knees burned, rendering him unable to stand; although the two were between life and death, they eventually recovered. Additionally, a fire broke out at the south eave of Seiryōden, and {{ill|Ukonoe Shigehide|ja|右近衛茂景}} single-handedly engaged in {{ill|firefighting|ja|消火}}.<ref name="kiryaku" /><ref name="fusob" /> According to the {{ill|Fusō Ryakki|ja|扶桑略記}}, an additional two members of the {{ill|Imperial Guard Office|ja|近衛府|lt=Guard|lt_ja=近衛}} were struck by lightning at Seiryōden.<ref name="fusof">『扶桑略記』本文 延長8年6月26日</ref>
