The lightning also struck the adjacent {{ill|Shishinden|ja|紫宸殿}}, and {{ill|Uhyōesa|ja|右兵衛佐}} Minu Tadakazusa (in the {{ill|Fusō Ryakki|ja|扶桑略記}}, identified as {{ill|Ukonoe Tadakane|ja|右近衛忠兼}} in that account) had his hair burned and died. Kikinren suffered burns to his abdomen and writhed in agony, and Azumi Sōjin had his knees burned, rendering him unable to stand; although the two were between life and death, they eventually recovered. Additionally, a fire broke out at the south eave of Seiryōden, and {{ill|Ukonoe Shigehide|ja|右近衛茂景}} single-handedly engaged in {{ill|firefighting|ja|消火}}.<ref name="kiryaku" /><ref name="fusob" /> According to the {{ill|Fusō Ryakki|ja|扶桑略記}}, an additional two members of the {{ill|Imperial Guard Office|ja|近衛府|lt=Guard|lt_ja=近衛}} were struck by lightning at Seiryōden.<ref name="fusof">『扶桑略記』本文 延長8th year 6月26日</ref>
