At that time, courtiers ({{ill|kuge|ja|Kugyō|12=draft|12=draft}}) and officials ({{ill|kanjin|ja|官人|12=draft|12=draft}}) present were caught up in the incident. Among the courtiers, {{ill|Dainagon|ja|大納言|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Minister of Popular Affairs|ja|民部省（律令制）|lt=Minbu-kyo|lt_ja=民部卿|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Fujiwara Kiyokan|ja|藤原清貫|12=draft|12=draft}} had his garments set on fire and his chest torn open, dying instantly, while {{ill|Right Middle-Border|ja|右中弁|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Internal Storage Head|ja|内蔵頭|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Taira Kiyose|ja|平希世|12=draft|12=draft}} suffered facial burns and was left in critical condition. Shortly after 16:30, as the rain ceased, Kiyokan was secretly transported by carriage from {{ill|Yōmyōmon|ja|陽明門|12=draft|12=draft}}, and Kiyose from {{ill|Shūmyōmon|ja|修明門|12=draft|12=draft}}; however, Kiyose soon died.
The lightning also struck the adjacent {{ill|Shishinden|ja|紫宸殿|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Uhyōesa|ja|右兵衛佐|12=draft|12=draft}} Minu Tadakazusa (in the {{ill|Fusō Ryakki|ja|扶桑略記|12=draft|12=draft}}, identified as {{ill|Ukonoe Tadakane|ja|右近衛忠兼|12=draft|12=draft}} in that account) had his hair burned and died. Kikinren suffered burns to his abdomen and writhed in agony, and Azumi Sōjin had his knees burned, rendering him unable to stand; although the two were between life and death, they eventually recovered. Additionally, a fire broke out at the south eave of Seiryōden, and {{ill|Ukonoe Shigehide|ja|右近衛茂景|12=draft|12=draft}} single-handedly engaged in {{ill|firefighting|ja|消火|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref name="kiryaku" /><ref name="fusob" /> According to the {{ill|Fusō Ryakki|ja|扶桑略記|12=draft|12=draft}}, an additional two members of the {{ill|Imperial Guard Office|ja|近衛府|lt=Guard|lt_ja=近衛|12=draft|12=draft}} were struck by lightning at Seiryōden.<ref name="fusof">『扶桑略記』本文 延長8th year 6月26日</ref>
