'''Seiryōden Lightning Strike Incident''' (清涼殿落雷事件) is a lightning strike disaster that occurred during the {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, in the 8th year of {{ill|Enchō (era)|ja|延長 (元号)|lt=Enchō|lt_ja=延長|qq=draft|qq=draft}} on {{ill|June 26 (lunar calendar)|ja|6月26日 (旧暦)|lt=June 26|lt_ja=6月26日|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|930 AD|ja|930th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|July 24|ja|7月24日|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) at {{ill|Heian-kyō|ja|平安京|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – {{ill|Imperial Palace|ja|内裏|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – at {{ill|Seiryōden|ja|清涼殿|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, where a lightning strike occurred.
== Overview == That year, the area around {{ill|Heian-kyō|ja|平安京|qq=draft|qq=draft}} was afflicted by a {{ill|drought|ja|旱魃|lt=Drought damage|lt_ja=干害|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and on June 26 a meeting of the {{ill|Great Council of State|ja|太政官|1=Daijō-kan|qq=draft|qq=draft}} was held at Seiryōden, where {{ill|Emperor Daigo|ja|醍醐天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft}} was present, to discuss whether to perform a {{ill|rainmaking ritual|ja|雨乞い|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref>『日本紀略』延長8th year 5月15日、6月</ref> However, shortly after noon, dark {{ill|cumulonimbus|ja|積乱雲|lt=black clouds|lt_ja=黒雲|qq=draft|qq=draft}} suddenly gathered above {{ill|Mount Atago (Kyoto)|ja|愛宕山 (京都市)|lt=Atago|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, covering Heian-kyō and unleashing a violent {{ill|thunderstorm|ja|夕立|lt=Thunderstorm|lt_ja=雷雨|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref name="kiryaku">『日本紀略』延長8th year 6月26日</ref> Shortly after 16:00, lightning directly struck the first pillar on the southwest side of Seiryōden.<ref name="fusob">『扶桑略記』裏書 延長8th year 6月26日</ref><ref name="kiryaku" />
At that time, courtiers ({{ill|kuge|ja|Kugyō|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) and officials ({{ill|kanjin|ja|官人|1=Kanjin|2=ja|3=官人|4=ko|5=관인|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) present were caught up in the incident. Among the courtiers, {{ill|Dainagon|ja|大納言|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Minister of Popular Affairs|ja|民部省（律令制）|lt=Minbu-kyo|lt_ja=民部卿|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Fujiwara Kiyokan|ja|藤原清貫|qq=draft|qq=draft}} had his garments set on fire and his chest torn open, dying instantly, while {{ill|Right Middle-Border|ja|右中弁|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Internal Storage Head|ja|内蔵頭|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Taira Kiyose|ja|平希世|qq=draft|qq=draft}} suffered facial burns and was left in critical condition. Shortly after 16:30, as the rain ceased, Kiyokan was secretly transported by carriage from {{ill|Yōmyōmon|ja|陽明門|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and Kiyose from {{ill|Shūmyōmon|ja|修明門|qq=draft|qq=draft}}; however, Kiyose soon died.
The lightning also struck the adjacent {{ill|Shishinden|ja|紫宸殿|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Uhyōesa|ja|右兵衛佐|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Minu Tadakazusa (in the {{ill|Fusō Ryakki|ja|扶桑略記|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, identified as {{ill|Ukonoe Tadakane|ja|右近衛忠兼|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in that account) had his hair burned and died. Kikinren suffered burns to his abdomen and writhed in agony, and Azumi Sōjin had his knees burned, rendering him unable to stand; although the two were between life and death, they eventually recovered. Additionally, a fire broke out at the south eave of Seiryōden, and {{ill|Ukonoe Shigehide|ja|右近衛茂景|qq=draft|qq=draft}} single-handedly engaged in {{ill|firefighting|ja|消火|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref name="kiryaku" /><ref name="fusob" /> According to the {{ill|Fusō Ryakki|ja|扶桑略記|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, an additional two members of the {{ill|Imperial Guard Office|ja|近衛府|lt=Guard|lt_ja=近衛|qq=draft|qq=draft}} were struck by lightning at Seiryōden.<ref name="fusof">『扶桑略記』本文 延長8th year 6月26日</ref>
