At that time, courtiers ({{ill|kuge|ja|Kugyō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/kuge|qq=}}) and officials ({{ill|kanjin|ja|官人|1=Kanjin|2=ja|3=官人|4=ko|5=관인|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/kanjin|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanjin|qq=}}) present were caught up in the incident. Among the courtiers, [[:en:Dainagon|Dainagon]] and {{ill|Minister of Popular Affairs|ja|民部省（律令制）|lt=Minbu-kyo|lt_ja=民部卿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minister of Popular Affairs|qq=}} {{ill|Fujiwara Kiyokan|ja|藤原清貫|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara Kiyokan|qq=}} had his garments set on fire and his chest torn open, dying instantly, while {{ill|Right Middle-Border|ja|右中弁|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Right Middle-Border|qq=}} and {{ill|Internal Storage Head|ja|内蔵頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Internal Storage Head|qq=}} {{ill|Taira Kiyose|ja|平希世|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira Kiyose|qq=}} suffered facial burns and was left in critical condition. Shortly after 16:30, as the rain ceased, Kiyokan was secretly transported by carriage from {{ill|Yōmyōmon|ja|陽明門|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yōmyōmon|qq=}}, and Kiyose from {{ill|Shūmyōmon|ja|修明門|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shūmyōmon|qq=}}; however, Kiyose soon died.
The lightning also struck the adjacent {{ill|Shishinden|ja|紫宸殿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shishinden|qq=}}, and {{ill|Uhyōesa|ja|右兵衛佐|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Uhyōesa|qq=}} Minu Tadakazusa (in the [[:en:Fusō Ryakuki|Fusō Ryakki]], identified as {{ill|Ukonoe Tadakane|ja|右近衛忠兼|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukonoe Tadakane|qq=}} in that account) had his hair burned and died. Kikinren suffered burns to his abdomen and writhed in agony, and Azumi Sōjin had his knees burned, rendering him unable to stand; although the two were between life and death, they eventually recovered. Additionally, a fire broke out at the south eave of Seiryōden, and {{ill|Ukonoe Shigehide|ja|右近衛茂景|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukonoe Shigehide|qq=}} single-handedly engaged in {{ill|firefighting|ja|消火|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/firefighting|qq=}}.<ref name="kiryaku" /><ref name="fusob" /> According to the [[:en:Fusō Ryakuki|Fusō Ryakki]], an additional two members of the {{ill|Imperial Guard Office|ja|近衛府|lt=Guard|lt_ja=近衛|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Guard Office|qq=}} were struck by lightning at Seiryōden.<ref name="fusof">『扶桑略記』本文 延長8th year 6月26日</ref>
