{{Infobox event | title = | image = | caption = Depicted in the “Kitano Tenjin Engi Emaki”, the Seiryōden Lightning Strike Incident | date = [[:en:Enchō|Enchō]]8th year {{ill|June 26 (Lunisolar)|lt=June 26 (Lunisolar)|lt=June 26 (lunar calendar)|ja|6月26日 (旧暦)|lt=June 26|lt_ja=6月26日|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 26 (lunar calendar)|qq=}} ([[:en:930|930 AD]] [[:en:July 24|July 24]]) | time = 16:00 - 16:30 | location = [[:en:Heian-kyō|Heian-kyō]] {{ill|Imperial Palace|ja|内裏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Palace|qq=}} {{ill|Seiryōden|ja|清涼殿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seiryōden|qq=}} | reported deaths = 3–5 persons ({{ill|Fujiwara Kiyokan|ja|藤原清貫|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara Kiyokan|qq=}}, {{ill|Taira Kiyose|ja|平希世|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira Kiyose|qq=}}, Minu Tadakazusa (美努忠包), {{ill|Imperial Guard Office|ja|近衛府|lt=Guard|lt_ja=近衛|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Guard Office|qq=}} 2 persons?) | reported injuries = 2–4 persons (Kikinren, Azumi Sōjin, 2 persons of Konoe?) | reported property damage = South eave of Seiryōden burned }}
'''Seiryōden Lightning Strike Incident''' (清涼殿落雷事件) is a lightning strike disaster that occurred during the [[:en:Heian period|Heian period]], in the 8th year of [[:en:Enchō|Enchō]] on {{ill|June 26 (Lunisolar)|lt=June 26 (Lunisolar)|lt=June 26 (lunar calendar)|ja|6月26日 (旧暦)|lt=June 26|lt_ja=6月26日|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 26 (lunar calendar)|qq=}} ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:930|930 AD]] [[:en:July 24|July 24]]) at [[:en:Heian-kyō|Heian-kyō]] – {{ill|Imperial Palace|ja|内裏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Palace|qq=}} – at {{ill|Seiryōden|ja|清涼殿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seiryōden|qq=}}, where a lightning strike occurred.
== Overview == That year, the area around [[:en:Heian-kyō|Heian-kyō]] was afflicted by a [[:en:Drought|Drought damage]], and on June 26 a meeting of the [[:en:Daijō-kan|Daijō-kan]] was held at Seiryōden, where [[:en:Emperor Daigo|Emperor Daigo]] was present, to discuss whether to perform a [[:en:Rainmaking (ritual)|rainmaking ritual]].<ref>『日本紀略』延長8th year 5月15日、6月</ref> However, shortly after noon, dark [[:en:Cumulonimbus cloud|black clouds]] suddenly gathered above [[:en:Mount Atago|Atago]], covering Heian-kyō and unleashing a violent {{ill|thunderstorm|ja|夕立|lt=Thunderstorm|lt_ja=雷雨|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/thunderstorm|qq=}}.<ref name="kiryaku">『日本紀略』延長8th year 6月26日</ref> Shortly after 16:00, lightning directly struck the first pillar on the southwest side of Seiryōden.<ref name="fusob">『扶桑略記』裏書 延長8th year 6月26日</ref><ref name="kiryaku" />
At that time, courtiers ({{ill|kuge|ja|Kugyō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/kuge|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) and officials ({{ill|kanjin|ja|官人|1=Kanjin|2=ja|3=官人|4=ko|5=관인|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/kanjin|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanjin|qq=}}) present were caught up in the incident. Among the courtiers, [[:en:Dainagon|Dainagon]] and {{ill|Minister of Popular Affairs|ja|民部省（律令制）|lt=Minbu-kyo|lt_ja=民部卿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minister of Popular Affairs|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} {{ill|Fujiwara Kiyokan|ja|藤原清貫|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara Kiyokan|qq=}} had his garments set on fire and his chest torn open, dying instantly, while {{ill|Right Middle-Border|ja|右中弁|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Right Middle-Border|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 弁官}} and {{ill|Internal Storage Head|ja|内蔵頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Internal Storage Head|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 内蔵寮}} {{ill|Taira Kiyose|ja|平希世|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira Kiyose|qq=}} suffered facial burns and was left in critical condition. Shortly after 16:30, as the rain ceased, Kiyokan was secretly transported by carriage from {{ill|Yōmyōmon|ja|陽明門|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yōmyōmon|qq=}}, and Kiyose from {{ill|Shūmyōmon|ja|修明門|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shūmyōmon|qq=}}; however, Kiyose soon died.
The lightning also struck the adjacent {{ill|Shishinden|ja|紫宸殿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shishinden|qq=}}, and {{ill|Uhyōesa|ja|右兵衛佐|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Uhyōesa|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 兵衛府}} Minu Tadakazusa (in the [[:en:Fusō Ryakuki|Fusō Ryakki]], identified as {{ill|Ukonoe Tadakane|ja|右近衛忠兼|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukonoe Tadakane|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in that account) had his hair burned and died. Kikinren suffered burns to his abdomen and writhed in agony, and Azumi Sōjin had his knees burned, rendering him unable to stand; although the two were between life and death, they eventually recovered. Additionally, a fire broke out at the south eave of Seiryōden, and {{ill|Ukonoe Shigehide|ja|右近衛茂景|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukonoe Shigehide|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} single-handedly engaged in {{ill|firefighting|ja|消火|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/firefighting|qq=}}.<ref name="kiryaku" /><ref name="fusob" /> According to the [[:en:Fusō Ryakuki|Fusō Ryakki]], an additional two members of the {{ill|Imperial Guard Office|ja|近衛府|lt=Guard|lt_ja=近衛|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Guard Office|qq=}} were struck by lightning at Seiryōden.<ref name="fusof">『扶桑略記』本文 延長8th year 6月26日</ref>
